# Interpreter for 'vpn-switch openvpn add <group> <target> <alias>' command
# Terminal function (_openvpn_add3) that creates symlinks in groups
#
# Default value: "sh"
#   Executes shell commands output by _openvpn_add3
#
# Function behavior:
#   Validates group directory exists
#   Validates target config exists
#   Creates symlink: ln -s "$target" "$VPN_SWITCH_BASE/openvpn/$group/$alias"
#
# This is part of a HETEROGENEOUS family (mixed terminal/combinator functions).
# See VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_wireguard_add for family-level documentation pattern.
